If you link Text-Editor then follow all below step:

step 1: Go to google tinymce
step 2: open first link "TinyMCE: The Most Advanced WYSIWYG HTML Editor ."
step 3: create account 
step 4: then generate Tiny API key

Tiny API Key is a unique token that links your TinyMCE instances to your account. It grants you access to all of our Premium Plugins during your free trial.

step 5: go to script file and add script src = " Your Own API key....."

step 6: In Html form add id in textarea if take id = anything.. this is your choice..
step 7 : put id name in script file in ---> selector: " your choose id name",

Done!
Thank You!